<Worksheet><Version major="6" minor="0"/><View-Properties><Zoom percentage="100"/></View-Properties><Styles><Layout alignment="centred" bullet="none" name="Author" spaceabove="8.0" spacebelow="8.0"/><Layout alignment="left" bullet="none" name="Heading 1" spaceabove="8.0" spacebelow="4.0"/><Layout alignment="left" bullet="none" firstindent="0.0" leftmargin="0.0" linebreak="space" name="Normal" rightmargin="0.0" spaceabove="0.0" spacebelow="0.0"/><Layout alignment="centred" bullet="none" name="Title" spaceabove="12.0" spacebelow="12.0"/><Font background="[0,0,0]" bold="false" family="Lucida Bright" foreground="[0,0,0]" italic="false" name="Text" opaque="false" size="12" underline="false"/><Font background="[0,0,0]" family="Lucida Bright" name="Author" opaque="false" size="12"/><Font background="[0,0,0]" bold="true" family="Serif" name="Heading 1" opaque="false" size="18"/><Font background="[0,0,0]" bold="true" executable="true" family="Monospaced" foreground="[255,0,0]" name="Maple Input" opaque="false" size="12"/><Font background="[0,0,0]" bold="true" family="Lucida Bright" name="Title" opaque="false" size="18" underline="true"/><Font background="[0,0,0]" executable="false" family="Lucida Bright" foreground="[0,0,0]" name="2D Math" opaque="false" size="12"/></Styles><Group><Input><Text-field firstindent="0.0" layout="Title" leftmargin="0.0" linebreak="space" rightmargin="0.0" style="Title"><Font executable="false" foreground="[0,0,0]" italic="false">Math243: Maple problem set #3.</Font></Text-field><Text-field firstindent="0.0" layout="Author" leftmargin="0.0" linebreak="space" rightmargin="0.0" style="Author"><Font bold="true" executable="false" foreground="[0,0,0]" italic="false" underline="true">Your name goes here.</Font></Text-field><Text-field firstindent="0.0" layout="Author" leftmargin="0.0" linebreak="space" rightmargin="0.0" style="Author">Due: 12 November 2003</Text-field><Text-field alignment="left" bullet="none" firstindent="0.0" layout="default" leftmargin="0.0" linebreak="space" rightmargin="0.0" spaceabove="8.0" spacebelow="8.0" style="default"><Font executable="false" style="Text">All solutions must be found using Maple.</Font></Text-field><Text-field alignment="left" bullet="none" firstindent="0.0" layout="default" leftmargin="0.0" linebreak="space" rightmargin="0.0" spaceabove="8.0" spacebelow="8.0" style="default"><Font background="[0,0,0]" family="Lucida Bright">This exercise uses<Font background="[0,0,0]" bold="true" family="Lucida Bright"> <Font background="[0,0,0]" bold="true" family="Lucida Bright">spacecurve, LinearAlgebra</Font></Font><Font background="[0,0,0]" family="Lucida Bright">.</Font></Font></Text-field></Input></Group><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="Heading 1">First things first.</Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">The first thing you should do with Maple is load in the packages you will need.  There's no harm in being careful and loading in things that you think you might need, even if you do not use them.</Text-field><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">with(LinearAlgebra):</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">with(plots):</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input"/></Input></Group></Section><Text-field/><Text-field/><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="Heading 1">Problem.</Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">Consider the space c<Font bold="false" italic="false" style="2D Math" underline="false">urve </Font><Equation input-equation="r(t) = ([8*exp(-t/5)*cos(t), 8*exp(-t/5)*sin(t), t])" style="2D Math">NiMvLUkickc2IjYjSSJ0R0YmNyUqKCIiKSIiIi1JJGV4cEdGJjYjLCQqJkYoRiwiIiYhIiJGM0YsLUkkY29zR0YmRidGLCooRitGLEYtRiwtSSRzaW5HRiZGJ0YsRig=</Equation><Font italic="false" style="Maple Input" underline="false"> </Font><Font bold="false" italic="false" style="2D Math" underline="false">over the domain </Font><Equation input-equation="[0, 4*Pi]" style="2D Math">NiM3JCIiISomIiIlIiIiSSNQaUdJKnByb3RlY3RlZEdGKUYn</Equation><Font bold="false" italic="false" style="2D Math" underline="false">.</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">Use Maple to find T, N and B on the curve at the points <Equation input-equation="t=0" style="2D Math">NiMvSSJ0RzYiIiIh</Equation><Font bold="false" italic="false" style="2D Math" underline="false">,  </Font><Equation input-equation="t=Pi/4" style="2D Math">NiMvSSJ0RzYiKiZJI1BpR0kqcHJvdGVjdGVkR0YoIiIiIiIlISIi</Equation><Font bold="false" italic="false" style="2D Math" underline="false">. and </Font><Equation input-equation="t=3*Pi/4" style="2D Math">NiMvSSJ0RzYiKigiIiQiIiJJI1BpR0kqcHJvdGVjdGVkR0YqRigiIiUhIiI=</Equation><Font bold="false" italic="false" style="2D Math" underline="false">.
Render the space curve and these vectors all together in the same plot.</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">Hint: The tangent vectors can be rendered as parametric lines using the information I emailed to everyone last week.</Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">The LinearAlgebra package is great for working with vectors, but Vectors do not work well with the plotting commands.</Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">You can convert a Vector to a list with the comman</Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text">You can convert a Vector to a list with the commands <Font bold="true">convert</Font>.</Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">myvector := &lt;sin(t),cos(t),t^2-t&gt;;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">spacecurve(myvector,t=0..2*Pi);  #Won't work!</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">mylist := convert(myvector,list);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">spacecurve(mylist,t=0..2*Pi);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input"/></Input></Group><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Text"/></Section><Text-field/><Text-field/><Text-field/><Text-field/><Text-field/><Text-field/></Worksheet>